programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Gravity

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Science and the Shuttle

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Landing on Mars

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Living with Space

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Atmosphere
programme.desc: Our atmosphere is an unbelievably complex machine that protects us from the vacuum of space, shelters us from harmful radiation and allows us and the biosphere to breath; we need to learn much more about it so we can better it.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Flight Status

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: Gear Lock

programme.desc: The Electra returns from repairs and the crew takes it right back to the ice strip that it set off from before the crash landing last year. Tyler works up the courage to confront Joe about a big decision. A hotshot Australian pilot tries to earn a job.

programme.desc: Facing Joe's wrath, Rod and Cory head to the UK to make urgent water bomber repairs. David tries to prove himself to Devan in the C-46 but ends up infuriating Devan. Will makes an ultimatum in Hay River.

programme.desc: Mikey trains for High Arctic survival with the Canadian Rangers. The Air Force invades Chuck's hangar. Joe faces tough competition at a California plane auction.

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: Frozen Solid
programme.desc: AJ and James battle a DC-4 engine fire. It's Joe's 69th birthday - and he's never flown a helicopter before, so Mikey plans a special gift of chopper flight lessons.

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: Breakdown

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: Air Show
programme.desc: Joe flies with the Snowbirds during the Hamilton air show and later teaches Mikey to fly. A surprise departure shakes up Buffalo.

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: Five Seasons

programme.title: Ice Pilots NWT: A Ball O'Snags

programme.title: 48 Hours: Abducted
programme.desc: Focuses on the accounts of two abductions that sparked a worldwide search.

programme.title: 48 Hours
programme.desc: A young banker named David Harmon was bludgeoned to death in his bed. Investigators came to believe that Melinda was involved in a secret affair with family friend Mark Mangelsdorf, and that the two were involved in David‚Äôs murder.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Dark Voyage
programme.desc: A report on events surrounding the mysterious death of aspiring actress Ashley Barnett on the cruise ship "Paradise" in October 2005.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Ghost of David Coffin
programme.desc: 48 Hours is television's most popular true-crime series, investigating shocking cases and compelling real-life dramas with journalistic integrity and cutting-edge style.

programme.title: 48 Hours
programme.desc: In September 2005, 17-year-old Taylor Behl, a Virginia Commonwealth University freshman, disappeared from campus. A police investigation eventually uncovered her association with Ben Fawley, a 38-year-old man who confessed to having sex with Taylor.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Murder Comes Knocking
programme.desc: In July 2004, Jarrod Davidson was shot to death outside his California apartment. Estranged from his ex-wife, Kelee, Jarrod had been seeking full custody of his daughter. After further investigation, Kelee‚Äôs parents were arrested for the murder of Jarrod.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Dangerous Reunion
programme.desc: In 1981, a series of sexual assaults targeting members of the Castleberry High cheerleading team occurred in and around River Oaks, Texas. Detectives quickly focused on Wesley Wayne Miller, former captain of the Castleberry High football team.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Murder on His Mind
programme.desc: Stephen Stanko murdered his girlfriend Laura Ling, and then raped and stabbed her daughter. Stanko‚Äôs defense was he had a brain defect and was temporarily insane.

programme.title: 48 Hours: A Storm of Murder
programme.desc: A report on the escalating murder rate in New Orleans during the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina and focusses on the January 2007 murder of filmmaker Helen Hill and the December 2006 murder of musician Dinerral Shavers.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Blood Feud
programme.desc: Nancy Seaman, an award-winning teacher living in Farmington Hills, Michigan was accused of the 2004 hatchet/stabbing murder of her husband, Bob. She admits killing him, but says it was self-defense, claiming that he had been abusing her for years.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Biggest Gamble
programme.desc: A report on the investigation into the October 2005 disappearance of Christine Wilson, a 27-year-old from Sacramento, California.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Defending Your Life
programme.desc: For 17 years, Kim and Beth Jones have been trying to prove that their father, Jerry Jones, Jr. is innocent of the 1988 murder of their mother, Lee. Jones was found guilty, but in 1999, the court ordered him released due to an ineffective lawyer.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Beyond the Boardwalk
programme.desc: A report on the deaths of four women: Tracy Ann Roberts, Kim Raffo, Barbara Briedor, and Molly Jean Dilts, all suspected prostitutes and/or drug addicts. They were all found on November 20, 2006, in a ditch near the Golden Key Motel in Atlantic City, NJ.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The McGuire Diaries
programme.desc: In May of 2004, Bill McGuire‚Äôs dismembered body was found in three suitcases in Chesapeake Bay. He had been shot with a .38 caliber gun. His wife Melanie claimed that Bill had vanished weeks before, after an argument.

programme.title: 48 Hours: A Mind For Murder
programme.desc: Carmin Murray was in the middle of a divorce and fighting over custody of Ciara, her 5- year-old daughter, when she was beaten and stabbed to death. Her husband Thomas, a university professor, became the main suspect.

programme.title: 48 Hours: The Puppet Master
programme.desc: A report on the marriage of Heather and Ron Samuels, who, even after divorcing, were involved in a bitter custody battle.

programme.title: 48 Hours: No Way Out
programme.desc: The owners of St. Rita's Nursing Home in St. Bernard Parish, La., are charged with negligent homicide after 35 residents died in the flood waters of Hurricane Katrina.

programme.title: 48 Hours: An Eye for An Eye
programme.desc: A report on the October 2004 murder of Dr. Brian Stidham, a pediatric eye surgeon in Tucson, Arizona, and the subsequent investigation which led to the trial and conviction of his colleague Dr. Bradley Schwartz.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Dangerous Liaisons
programme.desc: A report on the July 2003 murder of Sandra Rozzo of Pinellas Park, Florida, including the police investigation that led to the eventual conviction and imprisonment of her ex-lover Timothy ‚ÄòTracey‚Äô Humphrey and his wife Ashley Laney Humphrey.

programme.title: 48 Hours: Secrets of Palm Beach
programme.desc: A report about the murder of Linda Fishman, a wealthy widow found murdered in her Florida home. The childless woman had always been known for her generosity and at first it was suspected that her nephew was responsible for the crime.
